t171.text: Speaking from experience (as a Mayor during Black Sat) when the fires are out, communities start to recover. That's when the long, hard work begins. It won't be easy, but we know there are ways local councils can make it easier, which we learnt in 2009. Happy to share more info.

t172.text: Call on experts from the @bnhcrc, invite researchers at the Gender & Disaster centre to talk about their recovery guidelines, case studies of best practice. https://www.genderanddisaster.com.au/info-hub/research-resources/ …

t173.text: I suggest that the peak LG bodies in NSW, SA, Vic could organise a 1-day summit in the next month to share best practice on recovery. There are many fab speakers that could share their knowledge for the sake of traumatised communities. Ask Rob Gordon to deliver the keynote.

t174.text: Much was learnt from #BlackSaturday on how local councils could best support grieving, traumatised communities in the weeks, months and years following disaster. There have been papers, conferences and workshops on this topic, covering how to do it right and what NOT to do.
